                        </head><graphic url="w72-01.jpg"/></figure><p/></div><div><head>Discussion</head><bibl><ref type="biblio" target="Huwenhe1992">5</ref><note><p>Hu Wenhe identifies the Buddha figure in <hi rend="bold">72</hi> as Maitreya. </p></note></bibl><bibl><ref type="biblio" target="Li_Deng1997">44</ref><note><p>The authors give measurements for the cave and the Maitreya statue, with a short description.</p></note></bibl><bibl><ref type="biblio" target="ChengduKaoguFaxian2008">387–388</ref><note><p>The editors of the Chengdu Municipal Institute of Cultural Relics and Archaeology provide a detailed description of the architecture of cave <hi rend="bold">72</hi> and the statue on its main wall, including measurements.</p></note></bibl><bibl><ref type="biblio" target="LeeSonyaS2009">41; 73, note 17</ref><note><p>Lee includes niche <hi rend="bold">72</hi> in her cluster V, which corresponds to section E. She says that the style of the main Buddha’s halo was used throughout the Grove and can be found at all clusters.  </p></note></bibl></div></div></body></text></TEI>